  <li style="margin: 0.15rem 0;"></li>
</ul>

<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">4. To convert from degrees to radians, multiply by</h3>

<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">5. Madi’</h3>

<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">6. W radians</h3>

<h4 style="margin: 0 0 1rem 0; padding-left: 0.75rem; border-left: 4px solid #b91c1c; color: #000000; font-weight: 700;">Example 18: Angle D has a measure of 200°. If angle D can be written in its most simplified form as</h4>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">=i radians, where a and b are both integers, what is the value of a + b?</p>

<p style="margin: 0.3rem 0 0.5rem 0;">
