<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">conversion question, start with the given, which is 200°, and then use the conversion factor to change the</p>

<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">8. When we multiply by</h3>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">, the degree signs cancel, so we are left with radians. The question says angle D</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">can be written as 5 radians, so we can see thata = 10 andb =9. a+b = 19. The answer is C.</p>

