<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, Georgia, serif;">B. 40</span><br>
<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, Georgia, serif;">C. 48</span><br>
<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, Georgia, serif;">D. 56</span><br>
</p>

<p style="margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Third angle = 180° — 34° — 90° = 56°</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">The third angle we just found and x° are alternate interior angles, so they must be equal. The answer is D.</p>

