<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Sum of Interior Angles = 180°(n — 2) where n is the number of sides.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">It does not matter what the shape looks like. All that matters for the sum of the interior angles is the number of</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">sides. You can see how this works with the examples below:</p>

