<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">The ACT has commonly tested unit conversion questions on recent tests. When solving these questions,</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">always convert units BEFORE solving for any area or volume. For more advanced questions, knowing the</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">other conversion above can also be useful. The square yard, square feet, and square inches are used when</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">finding area while the cubic yard, cubic feet, and cubic inches are for volume.</p>

