<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">For similar triangles, the ratio of the side lengths is always the same:</p>

<h4 style="margin: 0 0 1rem 0; padding-left: 0.75rem; border-left: 4px solid #b91c1c; color: #000000; font-weight: 700;">Example 9: In triangle ABC, DE is parallel to BC, AE = 8, AC = 20, and AB = 18. What is the length</h4>

