<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">For A, we get ~~ Expressions with square roots are irrational numbers, so A is incorrect.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">For B, we get Va — 1. Expressions with square roots are irrational, so B is incorrect.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">ForC, we get 3Va. Again, square roots are irrational, so C is incorrect.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">For D, we get (Va)? = a. When you square a square root, the square root disappears. a is an</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">integer, which is a rational number, so D is correct.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">D is correct. All other answer choices have roots in the expression and are irrational.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Properties of Even and Odd Numbers</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">You should know the properties of even and odd numbers in the table below.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">While these may seem simple, knowing these properties can help with questions that ask about even and odd</p>

<h4 style="margin: 0 0 1rem 0; padding-left: 0.75rem; border-left: 4px solid #b91c1c; color: #000000; font-weight: 700;">Example 3: For the equation mn? + 3m = p, if m is a positive, even number and n is a negative, odd</h4>

