<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, Georgia, serif;">D. Positive and odd</span><br>
</p>

<p style="margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">numbers form and n. As long as we follow the rules in the question (m is positive and even, n is negative and</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">odd), we can pick any numbers. It is best to pick small numbers to make the algebra easier. Let’s pick m = 2</p>

