<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Once we have solved for y, we have found the inverse function. So, we can replace y with f~*(x).</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Now that we know the inverse, we can find f~1(6.5) by plugging in 6.5</p>

