<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">As with the Law of Sines rules we just learned, the Law of Cosines is a property of any triangle. Law of</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Cosines is used to find a missing side or angle in a non-right triangle. The Law of Cosines equation is</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">We use Law of Cosines when we do not have two pairs of angles and opposite side lengths. It is important to</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">notice that the a-value in the equation is the side length opposite the angle A. The other two side lengths, b</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">and c, are interchangeable since they do the same thing in the equation.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">On the ACT, you are not always given the Law of Cosines, so you need to memorize the equation. The</p>

