<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">21. Proportions</h3>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">On the ACT, you need to know the equations for two types of proportions: direct proportions and indirect</p>

<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">22. Direct Proportion</h3>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">In a direct <strong style="color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: underline;">proportion</strong>, y varies directly with x. In simpler terms, x and y will move together. As x increases,</p>

