<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Since we are given ZABD = 68° and ZACD = 40°, we can solve for 2CAB.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">The question tells us that AD is a bisector of ZCAB. A bisector cuts an angle in half, so we know that</p>

