<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Line g has a <strong style="color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: underline;">slope</strong> of —7. Since line p is perpendicular to line g, line p must have a <strong style="color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: underline;">slope</strong> of = The answer is</p>

