<h3 style="margin-top: 5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700;">66. Dividing Fractions</h3>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Let’s say that you are solving a question and get</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">To solve for x, we divide both sides by = How do we divide a fraction by a fraction? Take the fraction on</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">the bottom, flip it to get the reciprocal, and then multiply the reciprocal by the top fraction. This of</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">often referred to as “keep, flip, change.” It’s as easy as that!</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">We can use this method any time we are dividing by a fraction even if the right side is a whole number. For</p>

