<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Multiplying Perfect Squares — Don’t Forget to FOIL</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">When multiplying perfect squares, make sure to avoid the common mistake of forgetting to FOIL.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">To help avoid this mistake, you can write the perfect square as two expressions and then FOIL.</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">(x +5)? =(x+5)(x +5) = x2 4+5x+5x4</p>

<h4 style="margin: 0 0 1rem 0; padding-left: 0.75rem; border-left: 4px solid #b91c1c; color: #000000; font-weight: 700;">Example 1: Which of the following is equivalent to (2x + 3)? + 4x ?</h4>

<p style="margin: 0.3rem 0 0.5rem 0;">
<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, Georgia, serif;">A. 4x*+16x+9</span><br>
<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, Georgia, serif;">B. 4x*+4x+9</span><br>
<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, Georgia, serif;">C. 2x*+4x+3</span><br>
